<!--
Perceive-act loop, v2. The same shared always-socket agent (`agent.bsx`) and the same
in-process mock head as v1, but the mock body is swapped for a real wgpu body: a 3d fox
that drives off the model's `drive` command. That one client swap is the only change from
v1. Run it; the socket server default-boots and <WgpuBody> opens the render window:

    beet --main=examples/perceive_act/main-v2.bsx

`<WgpuBody>` opens a window with the fox over a ground plane and serves `drive` by feeding
the agent-chosen `DifferentialDrive` into the fox through the agnostic `SetDrive` leaf,
holding it for the chosen duration then stopping, the same command that will drive the v3
robot. The head still captures the floor-photo fixtures, speaks via `tts` and logs the chosen image.

Needs `OPENAI_API_KEY` (the agent) and the kokoro `tts` on PATH for spoken audio.
-->
<Fragment>
	<!-- the agent + fixtures live workspace-relative, so this entry roots there -->
	<StoreRoot src="../.."/>
	<CrateCheck features="thread,sockets,winit"/>
	<Template src="examples/perceive_act/agent.bsx"/>
	<!-- in-process clients, each its own socket root -->
	<MockHead url="ws://127.0.0.1:8338"/>
	<WgpuBody url="ws://127.0.0.1:8338"/>
</Fragment>
